  <sect1 id="gibbon-introduction">
    <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>
          &App; is a graphical frontend for 
          <ulink url="http://www.fibs.com/">FIBS</ulink>, the First Internet
          Backgammon Server or other compatible servers.  You can play online 
          against other players from all over the world.
        </para>
        <para>
          <indexterm><primary><acronym lang="en">SGF</acronym></primary></indexterm>
          &App; uses the portable 
          <ulink url="http://www.red-bean.com/sgf/"><acronym>SGF</acronym></ulink> 
          format for saving files.  This is the same format that
          <indexterm><primary>GNU Backgammon</primary></indexterm>
          <ulink url="http://www.gnubg.org/">GNU Backgammon</ulink> uses.  It is
          therefore easy for you to let GNU Backgammon analyse your matches after
          playing.
        </para>
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="gibbon-getting-started">
    <title>Getting Started</title>

    <sect2 id="getting-started-app-menu">
      <title>Starting &app; from the application menu</title>
      <para>
        <indexterm><primary>Gnome</primary></indexterm>
        If you use the <ulink url="http://www.gnome.org/">Gnome</ulink>
        desktop, you can start &app; from the
        <term><guimenu>Applications</guimenu> menu</term> by selecting
        <menuchoice><guisubmenu>Games</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Gibbon</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.  For other systems, &app; will be installed in a similar location.
      </para>
    </sect2>
